# SaveDataSystem

## Purpose
Owns the live save-data resource: a map of slot UUID → JSON document. On the first frame the
`EngineConfigSingletonComponent` is present, it creates `SaveDataSingletonComponent` by loading every
`<savedataPath>/SaveSlots/<uuid>.json` file (the filename stem is the slot UUID). Thereafter it applies
`SetSaveDataRequestOneFrameComponent` requests from the App: each request updates the in-memory slot
entry and rewrites the matching `<uuid>.json` file on disk. Returns early while the engine config is
absent.

When `savedataPath` is empty the singleton is still created (empty map) so requests have somewhere to
land, but no files are read or written — the same no-disk fallback `WindowConfigSystem` uses for the
Testing build.

## Persistence
On a save request the system writes `<savedataPath>/SaveSlots/<uuid>.json` with the request's JSON,
creating the `SaveSlots` directory when missing. File I/O goes through the shared `pg::FileUtils`
helpers. The startup load does not write anything back.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | Source of the savedata path; gates singleton creation |
| SetSaveDataRequestOneFrameComponent | read | App request carrying the slot UUID + new JSON |
| SaveDataSingletonComponent | write | Presence-check; created lazily once config exists, then updated in place |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SaveDataSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once from the SaveSlots folder; slot entries updated in place by save requests |

## Side Effects
- Reads every `<savedataPath>/SaveSlots/*.json` on startup.
- Writes `<savedataPath>/SaveSlots/<uuid>.json` on each save request.
